Lynis / Tiger will be used to audit the internal machines (only the hosts that are running unix OS). 
Nmap will be used to audit the internal network.
Nessus will be used to look for layer 7 vulnerabilities (mainly). 

2 hardware boxes will be needed to run the pfSense appliances and another 2 to run the SNORT appliances. 


https://docs.netgate.com/pfsense/en/latest/book/hardware/hardware-sizing-guidance.html

The minimum hardware requirements for pfSense 2.4.4-RELEASE-p2 are:

   - CPU 600 MHz or faster
    -RAM 512 MB or more
   - 4 GB or larger disk drive (SSD, HDD, etc)
  -  One or more compatible network interface cards
  -  Bootable USB drive or CD/DVD-ROM for initial installation
